Super Eagles Goalkeeper Maduka Okoye teammate at Sparta Rotterdam and compatriot, Emmanuel Emegha has sealed a five year deal with Belgian side, Royal Antwerp. Royal Antwerp made the announcement on their official website and it was stated that the Nigerian who had been capped by the Dutch national team at junior level debuted for Sparta when he was 17 years old last season and he played 35 league games for his ex-club before he left the club.   Liverpool’s duo Salah, Mane may face-off in AFCON Final on…     Awoniyi’s return boosts Union Berlin     Stallions seek Senegal upset in first semifinal   “The 18-year-old Emanuel Emegha just signed a contract for 5 seasons at the Bosuil. The Dutch promise international comes over from Sparta Rotterdam, where he enjoyed his youth training,” the club’s website said. “The young attacker made his professional debut at the highest level at Sparta last season, at the age of 17. He played 35 Eredivisie matches in that period. In addition, the center striker also plays for the Dutch national team U-19.”